betterquesting:10.desc:8:
What's with the numbers in the corner? That is an In-Game Info (IGI) mod. 
Some of the info it gives is useful right away, some of it shines later on in progression.

For now, the most important thing it does is showing if you are in an ore chunk. Further quests will explain what it means.

If you want to hide it, type "/igi disable" in the chat. 
Type "/igi enable" if you want to turn it back on.

§TThe command "/igi config" opens the configuration window to control its position, scale, and size.

The command "/xu_tps" toggles the Ticks Per Second (TPS) meter from the mod Extra Utilities.  
TPS is a measure of how well your server is running. The ideal TPS is 20. 
If TPS is less than 15, thing are going to start lagging noticeably. 
At TPS of 10 or less, it is going to be hard to play.
The tooltip shows three types of TPS: instantaneous, average, and worst-case.
If you need suggestions on solving TPS problems, feel free to ask for help in the GTNH Discord.
